    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "[Carl Sagan]\nLet&#39;s take a trip to examine", 
            "dur": "2.278", 
            "start": "7.629"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This common basis of life,", 
            "dur": "2.37", 
            "start": "9.907"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "A voyage to investigate the molecular machinery", 
            "dur": "3.65", 
            "start": "12.277"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "At the heart of life on Earth.", 
            "dur": "2.122", 
            "start": "15.927"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[David Attenborough]\nAll life is related.", 
            "dur": "3.077", 
            "start": "18.932"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And it enables us to construct with confidence", 
            "dur": "4.446", 
            "start": "22.301"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The complex tree that represents the history of life.", 
            "dur": "5.502", 
            "start": "27.438"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Our planet, the Earth, is as far as we know,", 
            "dur": "4.275", 
            "start": "36.498"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Unique in the universe- it contains life.", 
            "dur": "4.194", 
            "start": "40.977"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Here, plants and animals proliferate in such numbers", 
            "dur": "3.834", 
            "start": "46.145"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That we still have not even named all the different species", 
            "dur": "3.931", 
            "start": "50.328"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Darwin&#39;s great insight revolutionized the way in which we see the world", 
            "dur": "4.744", 
            "start": "54.706"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We now understand why there are so many different species", 
            "dur": "3.553", 
            "start": "59.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[Sagan]\nEvery cell is a triumph of natural selection", 
            "dur": "3.666", 
            "start": "64.384"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And we&#39;re made of trillions of cells\n(Within us is a little universe)", 
            "dur": "4.587", 
            "start": "68.05"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Those are some of the things that molecules do", 
            "dur": "4.154", 
            "start": "72.838"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Given 4 billion years of evolution", 
            "dur": "2.852", 
            "start": "76.992"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "(We are, each of us, a multitude)", 
            "dur": "2.771", 
            "start": "80.066"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now how did the molecules of life arise?", 
            "dur": "4.442", 
            "start": "86.103"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[Attenborough]\nIt began in the sea", 
            "dur": "1.749", 
            "start": "91.032"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Some 3,000 million years ago", 
            "dur": "2.761", 
            "start": "92.781"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Complex chemical molecules began to clump together", 
            "dur": "4.003", 
            "start": "95.542"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "These were the &quot;seeds&quot;", 
            "dur": "1.185", 
            "start": "100.581"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "From which the tree of life developed", 
            "dur": "2.143", 
            "start": "102.058"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They were able to split, replicating themselves", 
            "dur": "1.841", 
            "start": "104.419"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "As bacteria do", 
            "dur": "1.747", 
            "start": "106.849"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[Sagan]\nThe secrets of evolution ", 
            "dur": "1.812", 
            "start": "108.942"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "are time and death", 
            "dur": "2.38", 
            "start": "110.754"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "There&#39;s an unbroken thread that stretches", 
            "dur": "1.98", 
            "start": "113.478"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "from those first cells to us", 
            "dur": "2.096", 
            "start": "115.458"
        }, 
        {
